Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And I select 'DWI' from 'weighting' dropdown menu in Page 03 of Head MRI
And I go to Page 10 of Head MRI
And I select 'Finding' radio button
And I select 'Pathology' from the dropdown menu
And I select 'I describe' or 'I know' radio button

When I select 'Characterization I' tab
Then 'Circumscribed' radio button is enabled
And 'Non-circumscribed' radio button is enabled
And 'Nodular' radio button is enabled
And 'Multinodular' radio button is enabled

And 'Homogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Heterogeneous' radio button is enabled

And 'Round' radio button is enabled
And 'Oval' radio button is enabled
And 'Lobulated' radio button is enabled
And 'Patchy' radio button is enabled
And 'Areal' radio button is enabled

And 'T1w signal' slide bar is enabled
And 'T2w signal' slide bar is enabled
And 'FLAIR signal' slide bar is enabled

And 'Signal void' checkbox is enabled

And 'Diffusion restriction' checkbox is enabled

And 'Hemorrhage' checkbox is enabled
And 'Necrosis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Calcification' checkbox is enabled
And 'Fat' checkbox is enabled
And 'Cysts' checkbox is enabled
And 'Capsule' checkbox is enabled
And 'Septa' checkbox is enabled
And 'Signal voids' checkbox is enabled
And 'Fluid Level' checkbox is enabled
And 'Tooth/bone formation' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Circumscribed' radio button
Then 'Circumscribed' radio button is selected

When I select 'Non-circumscribed' radio button
Then 'Non-circumscribed' radio button is selected

When I select 'Nodular' radio button
Then 'Nodular' radio button is selected

When I select 'Multinodular' radio button
Then 'Multinodular' radio button is selected

When I select 'Homogeneous' radio button
Then 'Homogeneous' radio button is selected

When I select 'Heterogeneous' radio button
Then 'Heterogeneous' radio button is selected

When I select 'Round' radio button
Then 'Round' radio button is selected

When I select 'Oval' radio button
Then 'Oval' radio button is selected

When I select 'Lobulated' radio button
Then 'Lobulated' radio button is selected

When I select 'Patchy' radio button
Then 'Patchy' radio button is selected

When I select 'Areal' radio button
Then 'Areal' radio button is selected

When I move 'T1w signal' slide bar to 'Hyper-intense'
Then 'Hyper-intense' is selected on the slide bar

When I move 'T2w signal' slide bar to 'Hyper-intense'
Then 'Hyper-intense' is selected on the slide bar

When I move 'FLAIR Signal' slide bar to 'Hyper-intense'
Then 'Hyper-intense' is selected on the slide bar

When I select 'Signal void' checkbox
Then 'Calcification' radio button is enabled
And 'Blood' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Calcification' radio button
Then 'Calcification' radio button is selected

When I select 'Blood' radio button
Then 'Blood' radio button is selected

When I select 'Diffusion restriction' checkbox
Then 'Diffusion restriction' checkbox is selected

When I select all the 10 checkboxes under the section 'Internal structure'
Then all 10 checkboxes are selected
